main event: A civilian couple in Syosset, New York observed two unusual objects in the sky on July 16, 1960.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be at a great height and emitted a reddish-orange light.
The objects changed their course abruptly, sometimes appearing to stop or slow down.
The couple observed the objects for approximately 5-10 minutes.
Another former Air Force officer in the area also reported seeing the same objects at the same time.
The Air Force requested the couple fill out questionnaires for further evaluation of the sighting.
sighted object: Two unidentified high-altitude objects with reddish-orange lights
